episodes.title: Okoto no Chikai: Luffy to Kouzuki Momonosuke

episodes.title: Densetsu no Koukai: Inu to Neko to Kaizokuou!
episodes.plot: Dogstorm and Cat Viper share their story of being on the journey with Oden and Roger but are interrupted by Nami who is concerned about the sea route. Meanwhile, Jack is plotting to bring down the Mokomo Dukedom again.

episodes.title: Akumu Futatabi: Fujimi no Jack Kyoushuu
episodes.plot: The plans are set. The Straw Hats divide and conquer, one group heading to save Sanji, the others to the Land of Wano. But in the final moments before their departure, the tremendous elephant island begins to quake.

episodes.title: Zou Boueisen: Luffy to Zunesha!
episodes.plot: After being aggressively attacked by Jack's fleet, the monstrous Zunesha comes to life and beckons to those on its back. But can the Straw Hats understand its cry? And realize in time what the elephant island needs from them?

episodes.title: Zunesha o Sukue: Mugiwara Rescue Daisakusen!
episodes.plot: With the skirmish with Jack now over, the Straw Hats move on to trying to bandage the great elephant's wounds. But just as the whole island puts the plan into action, unseen danger lurks on horizon.

episodes.title: Wakare no Gezou: Sanji Dakkan no Funade!
episodes.plot: The Straw Hats and the others split up into four teams, each on different missions. Some from the Mink Tribe insist on leaving with Luffy's team. Meanwhile, Usopp makes a weapon for Nami that seems to work like magic.

episodes.title: Reverie e: Oujo Vivi to Shirahoshi-hime
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Reverie e: Rebecca to Sakura Oukoku
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Kaidou Futatabi: Kyoui Semaru Saiaku no Sedai!
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Harapeko Sensen: Luffy to Kaigun Rookie!
episodes.plot: After spotting an island the Straw Hat's stop to get some food. however the island is home to a marine base and Luffy and the others must disguise themselves as marines if they want to get inside.

episodes.title: Shuunen no 3 Nin: Mugiwara Ichimi Dai Chase!
episodes.plot: The jig is up as Luffy and the others make a daring dash to avoid the furious Navy. Can they escape without having to turn to fight - and after they've had a chance to raid the cabinets for food?

episodes.title: Akuma no Kobushi: Kessen! Luffy tai Grant
episodes.plot: Making a mad dash for the Submerge with the food they stole, Luffy and the others have to get through some of the Navy's upstart soldiers. Grount, whose arm holds incredible power, summons his training to challenge Luffy.

episodes.title: Sanji Kikyou: Big Mom no Nawabari e!
episodes.plot: The Straw Hats continue to suffer from blazing heat and a perilous food crisis. As the seas finally calm, fishing is their only hope. Meanwhile, Sanji arrives in Big Mom's territory and keeps his cool - until he sees his bride-to-be.

episodes.title: Rei to Yon: Souguu! Germa Double Six
episodes.plot: Luffy is in danger as the venomous fish poison courses through his body. With no antidotes on board, the Straw Hats must rely on a mysterious ship for help - a ship that bears a truly surprising crew.

episodes.title: Moudoku no Kiki: Luffy to Reiju!
episodes.plot: On the edge of life and death, Luffy's only hope rests with Sanji's siblings. But even though they refuse to share an antidote, they may be able to save Luffy's life yet, giving him enough energy to plunge right back into trouble.

episodes.title: Totto Land! Yonkou Big Mom Toujou
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Yonkou no Musume: Sanji no Fiancee Purin
episodes.plot: The Straw Hats confront Pudding - the fiancee of Sanji. But when they challenge her for Sanji's heart, her answer shocks them. Meanwhile an ominous and mysterious message may spell doom for the Straw Hats.

episodes.title: Dai Shingeki! Kui Wazurai no Mom
episodes.plot: The dangerous waters around the Whole Cake Island harbor terrifying creatures that pose a challenge for the Straw Hats. Meanwhile, Mama slips into a bout of her sickness and ravages her own land in search a specific pastry.

episodes.title: Shuto Houkai!? Big Mom to Jinbee
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Yonkou No Shiro: Whole Cake Island Touchaku
episodes.plot: Jinbei wants to leave Big Mom's crew but because Big Mom thinks of him as a powerful asset she wants him to lose something as well. Pedro tells the crew more about his past and the straw hats battle giant ants.

episodes.title: Okashi na Mori: Luffy tai Luffy!?
episodes.plot: The straw hats arrive at the whole cake island. Pedro and Brook take the Shark Submerge 3 while Luffy, Carrot, Nami and Chopper look for Sanji. The crew see Sanji and go after him but they get distracted by sweets except for Nami.

episodes.title: Mom no Shikaku: Luffy to Yuuwaku no Mori!
episodes.plot: Nami, Carrot and Chopper are chasing after Sanji, when doing so they meet a buried giant. The group is then attacked by a rabbit although the rabbit is not a Mink. Sanji fights one of his brothers.

episodes.title: Kaiyuu Kokka: Germa no Ou Judge
episodes.plot: Sanji beat his brother Yonji because of that Sanji's father, Judge Vinsmoke challenges him to a fight. A flashback reveals how Sanji's family mistreated and bullied him because they viewed him as weak.

episodes.title: Oyako Taiketsu: Judge tai Sanji!
episodes.plot: Sanji loses his fight with his father, Judge Vinsomoke, although Sanji doesn't think of him as his father at all.

episodes.title: Kyoudai na Yabou: Big Mom to Caesar
episodes.plot: News spread across the cake island about Jimbe in the newspaper. Pekom, captured by The Fire Tank Pirates was shot and falls off a cliff into sea full of sharks. Big Mom's plan for Caesar is revealed. Luffy is still stuck in the seducing woods.

episodes.title: Tamashii no Kuni: Mom no Osorubeki Nouryoku!
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Daikanbu! Sanshousei Cracker Toujou!
episodes.plot: The identity of the enigmatic Pound, the man half-buried in the woods, is revealed, but his deep connection to Big Mom might not be enough to save him. Nami's past exploits, however, hold the key to keeping Mom's minions at bay.

episodes.title: 8 Oku no Teki: Luffy tai Senshu no Cracker
episodes.plot: A battle between Luffy and Cracker (one of the Sweet 3 Generals) begins. Nami is educated on some of the history of those who came to challenge Big Mom before.

episodes.title: Zenryoku Shoubu: Gear Fourth tai Bisbis no Chikara
episodes.plot: Luffy continues to fight Cracker, and finds out that how troublesome his power can be. Brook and Pedro are on Cake Island and have to figure out how to move around the island without getting caught.

episodes.title: Ichi to Ni: Shuuketsu! Vinsmoke-ke
episodes.plot: The wind starts to go out of Luffy's sails as he starts to fight an endless army of Biscuit Warriors. Meanwhile, the oldest two Vinsmoke brothers come home from a war to see their long-missing young brother Sanji.

episodes.title: Onjin no Inochi: Sanji to Owner Zeff
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Ikari no Sanji: Germa Double Six no Himitsu
episodes.plot: Luffy needs just 10 minutes to recharge. Nami comes to rescue with the help of the Homies. Meanwhile, Sanji learns the terrible truth of Germa's power - and his father's dark history.

episodes.title: Suteta Kako: Vinsmoke Sanji
episodes.plot: Nami challenges Cracker on her own. During the all-out fight, she loses her advantage and is close to defeat. Can Luffy bounce back in time? Meanwhile, Sanji's tragic childhood is made clear.

episodes.title: East Blue e: Sanji Ketsui no Funade
episodes.plot: The terrible history of Sanji's family continue to unfold. From a rare moment of compassion he is able to escape, only to face his father's cruelty before setting out on his own.

episodes.title: Genkai Shoubu: Luffy to Mugen Biscuit
episodes.plot: Luffy and Sweet Comander Cracker continue their fight, with this time, someone's insatiable hunger taking advantage of an infinity of biscuits.

episodes.title: Manpuku no Chikara: Shin Gear Fourth Tan Man!
episodes.plot: Luffy filled with Cracker's biscuit, unlocks a new Gear Fourth attack that sends Cracker flying but it is not without consequences. Chopper and Carrot locate Sanji's reflection in one of Brûlée's mirror and try to communicate with him

episodes.title: Kanashiki Kettou: Luffy tai Sanji (Zenpen)
episodes.plot: Sanji and luffy undertake an emotional battle when luffy finally meets sanji and tries to get him back to the crew.

episodes.title: Kanashiki Kettou: Luffy tai Sanji (Kouhen)
episodes.plot: Luffy refuses to fight Sanji, because of this Sanji beats Luffy. When Sanji is leaving Luffy tells him that he doesn't believe he meant what he said and that he'd be waiting for him.

episodes.title: Fukushuu no Arashi: Ikari no Gundan Shuurai!
episodes.plot: Because Luffy beat Cracker Big Mom becomes enraged so she sends her enraged army to deal with him. The Vinsmokes arrive at the Whole Cake Chateau and have a feast with Big Mom.

episodes.title: Bouken no Owari: Sanji Ketsui no Propose
episodes.plot: Luffy faces Big Mom's enraged army. Nami and King Baum come back to help. In the Mirro-World, Randolph begins attacking Chopper and Carrot. Sanji agrees to marry pudding.

episodes.title: Koko de Matsu: Luffy tai Ikari no Gundan
episodes.plot: Chopper and Carrot fight against Brulee. Sanji makes a deal with Big Mom to spare his friends. Luffy continues fighting.

episodes.title: Chateau Sennyuu: Ubae! Road Ponegliff
episodes.plot: Tamago increases security on the Poneglyphs. Brook and Pedro hatch a plan. Chopper and carrot get captured. Luffy finds himself inside a book.

episodes.title: Innnen no Taimen: Luffy to Big Mom!
episodes.plot: Big mom talks to Luffy. Sanji is worried about Luffy and his crew mates. Baron and Smoothie guards the treasure room. Pedro distracts the enemies.

episodes.title: Tamashii no Sakebi: Brook & Pedro Dengeki Sakusen
episodes.plot: Brook manages to sneak into the Room of Treasure with the help of Pedro. While Sanji picks flowers for Pudding, she goes to the Prisoner Library to visit Luffy and Nami.

episodes.title: Sayonara: Purin Namida no Ketsui
episodes.plot: Pudding reveals a secret plan to prevent Sanji from marrying her, shocking Luffy and Nami and leaves saying goodbye. Brook defeats all the guards in treasure room. Tamago confronts Pedro in the third floor courtyard.

episodes.title: Hidari Me no Innen: Pedro tai Tamago-Danshaku
episodes.plot: Chopper and carrot try to find a way out. Brook prepares to fight Big Mom. Pedro fights with baron and remembers how he fought him five years ago with Zepo.

episodes.title: Shikemoku: Sanji no Kekkon Zen'ya
episodes.plot: Luffy tries to get out of the book. Sanji makes a dish for pudding. A shocking truth is revealed about her.

episodes.title: Fukutsu no Soul: Brook tai Big Mom
episodes.plot: Reiju forgot how she ended up hurt. Brook is confronted by big mom. Chopper finds a way out of mirror world. Luffy is saved from prison library.

episodes.title: Sora no Negai: Germa no Shippaisaku Sanji
episodes.plot: Sanji reveals the truth to Reiju. Reiju tells him about their mother.
